        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(feishu): add pagination support for drive list and info",
        "body": "Closes #93928\n\n## What Problem This Solves\n\nFeishu drive list and info lacked pagination - when a folder had more than 10 items, list returned only the first page and info returned File not found for items beyond the first page.\n\n## Why This Change Was Made\n\nAdded page_size, page_token, and all parameters to the drive schema. listFolder loops through pages with MAX_LIST_PAGES = 100 guard. getFileInfo searches all pages before concluding the file is missing.\n\n## Evidence\n\n```text\nFeishu drive schema pagination test:\nSchema compiles: Type.Union with 3 variants\nParams: page_size, page_token, all supported\nMAX_LIST_PAGES = 100 (infinite loop protection)\n```\n\nNot tested: End-to-end with a real Feishu tenant (requires tenant credentials).",
